      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Soak the fruit (night before)",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Combine {{sultanas}}, {{raisins}}, {{currants}}, {{glace-cherries}}, and {{mixed-peel}} in a large bowl. Pour over {{orange-juice}}. Stir, cover, and leave overnight at room temperature. The fruit should absorb most of the liquid.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake the cake",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Heat the oven to 140°C fan (160°C conventional). Line a deep 20 cm round tin with a double layer of baking paper on the base and sides, with the paper extending 5 cm above the tin edge.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Beat {{unsalted-butter}} and {{muscovado-dark}} together in a large bowl until pale and fluffy, about 3 to 4 minutes with an electric mixer. Add {{black-treacle}} and mix briefly.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Add {{eggs}} one at a time, beating well between each addition. If the mixture curdles, add a tablespoon of flour with each egg.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Sift together {{plain-flour}}, {{mixed-spice}}, {{cinnamon-ground}}, and {{ginger-ground}}. Fold into the butter mixture until just combined.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Add the soaked fruit and any remaining soaking liquid. Add {{almonds}} and fold everything together.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Spoon into the prepared tin and level the surface. Wrap the outside of the tin with a double layer of brown paper tied with string. Bake for 2.5 to 3 hours. After 1.5 hours, check and cover the top loosely with foil if it is browning too fast.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "The cake is done when a skewer comes out clean and the edges have pulled away slightly from the tin. Leave to cool completely in the tin before removing. Store wrapped in baking paper in a tin at room temperature.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "To finish",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Brush the top and sides of the cake with warmed apricot jam, then cover with rolled marzipan. Leave the marzipan to dry for 24 hours, then cover with royal icing or ready-to-roll fondant. Dust with icing sugar or decorate as you like.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
